title: -The Total Neutron Cross Section of Fe-54 In The Kev Energy Region.- (In German)

x4codes.shortRef: Rept: Report from Euratom-countries + Euratom to EANDC, No.145 (1972)
Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.240, p.29 (1975)

x4freetext: -THE TOTAL NEUTRON CROSS SECTION OF FE-54 IN THE
KEV ENERGY REGION.- (IN GERMAN)
3 MV PULSED VAN DE GRAAFF ACCELERATOR.
TIME OF FLIGHT, TRANSMISSION MEASUREMENT.
FLIGHT PATH 4.962 M, PULSE WIDTH 1 NS, REPETITION
RATE 250 KHZ, CHANNEL WIDTH 2 NS.
.EXPERIMENTAL CROSS SECTIONS WERE CALCULATED FROM
MEASURED TRANSMISSION T AS  SIGMA = -LOG(T)/N  WHERE
N IS TOTAL NUMBER OF SAMPLE ATOMS PER BARN. THUS THEY
ARE RESOLUTION-BROADENED AND GIVEN PER SAMPLE ATOM
(INCLUDING ISOTOPIC IMPURITIES AND OXYGEN IN FE2O3).
MULTI-LEVEL R-MATRIX PARAMETERS WERE DETER-
MINED BY LEAST-SQUARES FIT SIMULTANEOUSLY TO THIN-
AND THICK-SAMPLE TRANSM. DATA (CODE FANAL2, FROEHNER).
.UNBROADENED CROSS SECTION OF PURE FE-54 WAS THEN
GENERATED FROM RESONANCE PARAMETERS.
.TRANSMISSION DATA, FITS AND CALCULATED PURE FE-54
CROSS SECTIONS ARE PLOTTED IN KFK-1516, FIGS. 1-3.
.SOMEWHAT MORE COMPLETE RESONANCE PARAMETER TABLES
(INCLUDING MEASURED RADIATION WIDTHS) ARE GIVEN IN
KFK-2046, -NEUTRON CAPTURE IN THE KEV ENERGY RANGE
IN STRUCTURAL MATERIALS FOR FAST REACTORS,-
PROC. OF A NEACRP-NEANDC SPECIALIST MEETING,
KARLSRUHE, MAY 1973.
.(SEE EXFOR ENTRY 20374)
HH REF ADDED
.TRANSMISSIONS ARE CORRECTED FOR BACKGROUND AND DEAD
TIME.
.ERRORS OF EXP. CROSS SECTIONS ARE STATISTICAL.
``   `` RESONANCE ENERGIES   `` MAINLY SYSTEMATICAL,
DUE TO TIMING UNCERTAINTIES.
``   `` RESONANCE WIDTHS ARE DUE TO CROSS SECTION
ERROR (COUNTING STATISTICS) PROPAGATED
THROUGH LEAST-SQUARES FIT.
``   `` CALCULATED CROSS SECTIONS ARE DUE TO WIDTH
UNCERTAINTIES, INDICATIVE ONLY (ENERGY
ERRORS AND CORRELATIONS NEGLECTED).
CROSS SECTIONS ARE CALCULATED FROM PARAMETERS AND
DOES NOT TAKE INTO ACCOUNT THE
ENERGY SCALE UNCERTAINTY (0.3 PERCENT) AND ERROR
COVARIANCES.
.POTENTIAL SCATTERING PARAMETERS OF KFK-1516 WERE
REPLACED BY NEW SET VALID FOR ENTIRE ENERGY RANGE,
A = 4.0+-0.3 FM  (R-MATRIX CHANNEL RADIUS),
S =(12+-1)/10**4 (DISTANT-LEVEL STRENGTH FUNCTION).
ALL RADIATION WIDTHS WERE ASSUMED AS GG = 2.0+-0.5 EV.
TO NEUDADA.
COMMENT WRITTEN.
